project.name: Logistic Domain v2
project.description: This is the improved version of the classical Logistic Domain

actor.name: Truck
actor.description: The agent truck moves from an origin place to a desination place.

useCase.name: Drive a Truck
useCase.description: The agent truck moves from an origin place to a desination place, in a city.

definition.precondition: - the truck must be at the origin place; - both places must be in the city.
definition.postcondition: - the truck is at the destination place.

useCase.name: Truck loads a Package
useCase.description: The agent truck loads a package at a place, which can be either a location or an airport.

definition.precondition: - the truck and the package must at the same place; - there must be space for the package in the truck;
definition.postcondition: - the package is in the truck; - the truck load is increased.
definition.invariants: - the truck remains at the same place.

useCase.name: Truck unloads a Package
useCase.description: The agent truck unloads a package at a place, which can be either a location or an airport.

definition.precondition: - the truck must be at the place; - the package must be in the truck.
definition.postcondition: - the package is at the place; - the truck load is decreased.
definition.invariants: - the truck remains at the same place.

useCase.name: Fly an Airplane
useCase.description: The agent airplane flies from an origin airport to a destination airport.

definition.precondition: - the airplane must be at the origin airport;
definition.postcondition: - the airplane is at the destination airport.

useCase.name: Airplane loads a Package
useCase.description: The agent airplane loads a package at an airport.

definition.precondition: - the airplane and the package must at the airport; - there must be enough space in the airplane;
definition.postcondition: - the package is in the airplane; - the airplane load is increased.
definition.invariants: - the airplane remains at the airport.

useCase.name: Airplane unloads a Package
useCase.description: The agent airplane unloads a package at an airport.

definition.precondition: - the airplane must be at the airport; - the package must be in the airplane.
definition.postcondition: - the package is at the airport; - the airplane load is decreased.
definition.invariants: - the airplane remains at the same place.

state.name: Airplane ready to load or unload
Truck ready to load or unload

action.precondition: truck.at = from and from.inCity = city and to.inCity = city

problem.name: LogisticTwoPackages
